my steps:
A)  create templates (client side) 
    1)  html
    2)  css
    3)  javascript

B)  server side:
    1)  create package.json
    2)  use express js
    3)  use ejs
    4)  data path throw 
    5)  middleware and security
    6)  public static item
    7)  join to DB using [mongodb Atlas] 
    8)  API get post put
    9)  express router & MVC  

    block steps:
    1)  frontend block:  [html   -   css -   javascript]
    2)  backend block:   [expressjs - ejs - datapath & middleware &  security   -   static items]
    3)  DataBase:   create DB - connection  - schema - model - API & express router - MVC
    


coder : Junior Developer or Junior Programmer
programmer: are involved in a specific part of the project.
developer: involved with a greater understanding of the full project scope.


https://www.software.ac.uk/blog/2016-10-06-coder-programmer-or-software-developer-spot-difference

every instance should have
1)  views for an instance       [html - css - javascript - ejs]
2)  model for data              [db - schema - model]
3)  routefile for routes        [express - routers]
4)  controller for the handlers [get - post - put - delete]

5)  partials                    [head - nav - footer]
6)  public staic items          [styles - images - javascript - etc]
7)  404 page 